*.key

# Live SQLite database. The bot WRITES to this file at runtime
# (chat_history, feedback, learned_patterns), so tracking it in git
# means every redeploy fights with whatever the production process
# has been logging. Instead, app.py auto-runs seed_db.py the first
# time it boots against an empty database (`courses` table empty).
data/edubot.db
data/edubot.db-journal
data/edubot.db-shm
data/edubot.db-wal

# DO commit these so first deploy is instant:
#   models/*.pkl          (trained classifier + vectoriser)
#   models/model_info.txt
# Render free tier has ephemeral disk; without these, every cold
# start would have to retrain. Keeping them in git makes the bot
# snappy from the first request after a deploy. If a local retrain
# changes them, commit the refreshed binaries explicitly.
